        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 27 at 3:58PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 358 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cox, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Darien, Ridgeville, Carnigan, Meridian, Valona, Wolf Island,
Little Saint Simons Island, Sapelo Island, Eulonia and Ashintilly.

This includes I-95 in Georgia near mile marker 50...and
between mile markers 47 and 49...and
between mile markers 51 and 59.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
